                                        <p>The short answer is:</p>
                                        <h4>I've kept homemade ice cream in my freezer for months and still enjoyed it.</h4>
                                        <p>The long answer:</p>
                                        <ul class="list clearfix">
                                            <li>Freezers' freeze-thaw cycles (basically, temperature fluctuations) slowly affect the consistency/iciness of homemade ice cream.</li>
                                            <li>Which is to say, homemade ice cream is theoretically better sooner rather than later.</li>
                                            <li>So, you could make it now, serve it on Thanksgiving, and it would be great.</li>
                                            <li>Or you could make it in a week or another week.</li>
                                            <li>Really, whatever's best with your schedule! (Either way, just make sure to let it sit out for a few minutes before serving, so it's easily scoopable.)</li>
                                        </ul>
