                                        <ul class="list clearfix">
                                            <li>Some folks devote ice cube trays to egg whites, slipping one in each indentation so they know exactly how many they have.</li>
                                            <li> Just so you know, one large egg white is about 2 tablespoons and weighs 25 grams. </li>
                                            <li>  I often freeze the whites in plastic containers, then slip them out of the containers, once frozen, then wrap them in plastic and secure them in zip-top freezer bags – with the quantity and date written on the outside.</li> 
